### ZimCrimeWatch API — REST Client Test File
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client, JetBrains HTTP Client
###
### USAGE
### ─────
### 1. Run Login first — copy the returned `access` and `refresh` tokens
### 2. Paste them into @accessToken / @refreshToken below
### 3. Run any other request
###
### New in this revision
### ─────────────────────
### • POST /api/public/auth/register/         — self-registration
### • POST /api/public/auth/forgot-password/  — request reset token
### • POST /api/public/auth/reset-password/   — set new password
### • POST /api/zrp/auth/change-password/     — authenticated change
###

@baseUrl       = http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
@contentType   = application/json
@accessToken   = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken  = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
@badgeNumber   = 1234
@password      = qwerty1234


###############################################################################
# 1. AUTHENTICATION
###############################################################################

### 1.1 Login — obtain access + refresh token pair
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/login/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 1.2 Register — create a new officer account (role = officer by default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/register/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username":         "constable_nyasha",
  "first_name":       "Nyasha",
  "last_name":        "Moyo",
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-5544",
  "password":         "SecurePass@2025",
  "password_confirm": "SecurePass@2025"
}

###

### 1.3 Register — password mismatch (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/register/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username":         "constable_test",
  "first_name":       "Test",
  "last_name":        "Officer",
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-9999",
  "password":         "Password@1",
  "password_confirm": "Password@2"
}

###

### 1.4 Register — duplicate badge number (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/register/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username":         "duplicate_user",
  "first_name":       "Dupe",
  "last_name":        "User",
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}",
  "password":         "SecurePass@2025",
  "password_confirm": "SecurePass@2025"
}

###

### 1.5 Forgot Password — request a reset token
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/forgot-password/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}"
}

###

### 1.6 Forgot Password — badge number not found (same generic response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/forgot-password/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-000000-NONEXISTENT"
}

###

### 1.7 Reset Password — set a new password using the token from step 1.5
### Replace RESET_TOKEN_HERE with the token returned in 1.5
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/reset-password/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}",
  "token":            "RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
  "new_password":     "NewSecure@2025!",
  "confirm_password": "NewSecure@2025!"
}

###

### 1.8 Reset Password — password mismatch (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/reset-password/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}",
  "token":            "anytoken",
  "new_password":     "Password@1",
  "confirm_password": "Password@2"
}

###

### 1.9 Change Password (authenticated — must be logged in)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/auth/change-password/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_password": "{{password}}",
  "new_password":     "NewSecure@2025!",
  "confirm_password": "NewSecure@2025!"
}

###

### 1.10 Change Password — wrong current password (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/auth/change-password/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_password": "wrongpassword",
  "new_password":     "NewSecure@2025!",
  "confirm_password": "NewSecure@2025!"
}

###

### 1.11 Token Refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/token/refresh/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refresh": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.12 Logout — blacklist the refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/logout/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refresh": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.13 Login — invalid credentials (expect 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/login/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-000000",
  "password":         "wrongpassword"
}


###############################################################################
# 2. PUBLIC ENDPOINTS (no authentication required)
###############################################################################

### 2.1 Get all anonymized crime map pins
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.2 Filter public crimes by crime_type_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?crime_type_id=1
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.3 Filter public crimes by suburb
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?suburb=Mbare
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.4 Filter public crimes by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-12-31
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.5 Get all crime types (used by Flutter filter sheet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crime-types/
Accept: {{contentType}}


###############################################################################
# 3. ZRP DASHBOARD — INCIDENT CRUD
###############################################################################

### 3.1 List all incidents
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.2 Filter by crime type + status
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/?crime_type_id=1&status=under_investigation
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 3.3 Create a new incident
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "case_number":            "ZRP-2025-00999",
  "crime_type":             1,
  "timestamp":              "2025-06-15T14:30:00Z",
  "latitude":               -17.8292,
  "longitude":              31.0522,
  "suburb":                 "Mbare",
  "description_narrative":  "Suspect stole laptop bag from parked vehicle.",
  "modus_operandi":         "Smash and grab — parked vehicles near busy market.",
  "status":                 "reported",
  "weapon_used":            "None",
  "num_suspects":           2
}

###

### 3.4 Get a single incident
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 3.5 Update an incident (partial PATCH-style)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "under_investigation",
  "serial_group_label": "Mbare Laptop Gang 2025"
}

###

### 3.6 Get similar incidents (Profile Matcher)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/similar/?top_n=5
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 3.7 Access without token (expect 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Accept: {{contentType}}


###############################################################################
# 4. CRIME TYPES
###############################################################################

### 4.1 List all crime types with incident counts
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 4.2 Create a crime type (analyst/admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name":        "Cybercrime",
  "description": "Crimes involving computers, networks, or digital devices.",
  "icon":        "💻"
}

###

### 4.3 Get a single crime type
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


###############################################################################
# 5. DASHBOARD KPI
###############################################################################

### 5.1 Dashboard summary (KPI cards)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/dashboard/summary/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


###############################################################################
# 6. ANALYTICS
###############################################################################

### 6.1 Generate KDE heatmap
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/heatmap/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "crime_type_id": 1,
  "start_date":    "2024-01-01",
  "end_date":      "2024-12-31",
  "bandwidth":     0.01
}

###

### 6.2 Heatmap — all crime types, no date filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/heatmap/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 6.3 Time series (weekly)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/timeseries/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "freq":       "W",
  "start_date": "2024-01-01",
  "end_date":   "2024-12-31"
}

###

### 6.4 Time series (monthly)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/timeseries/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "freq":       "M",
  "start_date": "2023-01-01",
  "end_date":   "2024-12-31"
}

###

### 6.5 Hotspot detection
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/hotspots/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 6.6 Profile Match
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/profile-match/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "incident_id": 1,
  "top_n":       5
}


###############################################################################
# 7. SERIAL CRIME LINKAGE
###############################################################################

### 7.1 Train the serial linkage model (DBSCAN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/serial-linkage/train/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 7.2 Get cluster assignments
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/serial-linkage/cluster/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 7.3 Link probability between two incidents
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/serial-linkage/link-probability/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "incident_id_a": 1,
  "incident_id_b": 2
}


###############################################################################
# 8. ADMIN — USER MANAGEMENT
###############################################################################

### 8.1 List all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 8.2 Create a new analyst account (admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username":         "asmith",
  "first_name":       "Alice",
  "last_name":        "Smith",
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-009999",
  "password":         "Analyst@2025!",
  "role":             "analyst"
}

###

### 8.3 Promote a registered officer to analyst
PUT {{baseUrl}}/zrp/users/2/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "role": "analyst"
}

###

### 8.4 Deactivate a user account (soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/zrp/users/3/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 8.5 Non-admin tries to access user list (expect 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


###############################################################################
# 9. ML TRAINING
###############################################################################

### 9.1 Trigger ML training (auto-selects supervised or unsupervised)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/ml/train/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 9.2 Without admin role (expect 403)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/ml/train/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}


###############################################################################
# 10. CSV BULK UPLOAD
###############################################################################

### 10.1 Upload crime data CSV (multipart — use REST Client or Postman)
### POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/data/upload-csv/
### Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
### Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----ZCWBoundary
###
### ------ZCWBoundary
### Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="crimes.csv"
### Content-Type: text/csv
###
### < /path/to/your/zimcrime_watch_dataset.csv
### ------ZCWBoundary--
